{
  "type": "doc",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left",
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Getting Started Quick Guide"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Follow the guide below and you'll be up and running in 15 minutes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "If you close this guide, you can always get back to it by clicking the \"Getting Started\" project in the sidebar. Once you're comfortable, you can archive this project and its associated tickets."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "First, we'll show you two important concepts on the Orcha platform. Then you will be asked to do a few items"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " to complete your onboarding."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left",
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Concept 1: Structural relationship between Projects, Workflows, Products, Tickets"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Each ticket is associated with a product, a workflow, and a project. You can set priorities using these attributes and Autopilot will generate the schedules. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Example below:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "attrs": {
        "src": "https://upload.staging-orcha.com/organization/15/e1e267e3d507cc942c34c25b226987fabaf946a2afe749c17d34c26723cf2bea",
        "alt": null,
        "title": null
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "blockquote",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "attrs": {
            "textAlign": "left"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A product can also pick which workflows are allowed. For example, A Marketing Website product is unlikely to have the same workflows as a Mobile Application."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "center"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "textStyle",
              "attrs": {
                "color": "#16a34a"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "text": "--- You now understand what information a ticket requires to be published ---"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left",
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Concept 2: Ticket lifecycle versus workflows"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Tickets go through their own lifecycle on Orcha. Before a ticket can be scheduled, it must have all assignees provide estimates for their portion of the work. Once a ticket is scheduled, it moves through the assigned workflow until it's completed. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "It's important to ensure that your product is accessible and inclusive to all users. Research best practices for accessibility in digital design, and consider seeking input from users with diverse abilities."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "attrs": {
        "src": "https://upload.orcha.io/organization/1/b8a1643b5e5d93ac067d16ebce9bb9c5cbadb9d2d4c56454f3503df3108e9d94",
        "alt": null,
        "title": null
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "center"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "textStyle",
              "attrs": {
                "color": "rgb(22, 163, 74)"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "text": "--- You now understand what information the scheduler requires to schedule tickets. Only scheduled tickets get worked on ---"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left",
        "level": 2
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": "left"
      }
    }
  ]
}
